 Similarly, for entertainment, censorship and introduction of internet can
 create new competitions (congestion).
 For housing, new constructions and overpopulation can cause congestion.
 These are commodity-specific instances and a focus on selected items may
 be the only way to test whether the changes in consumption patterns for
 the chosen commodity are explained by new scarce items and the competition
 caused for them.
 The data from Tanzania - so far - only seems to point that availability
 of services in urban and rural area can potentially cause some congestion
