\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 in B.
 The consumption can be standardized and compared only by talking about
 the proportions spent on each such-utility.
 This assumes the utility to be separable (so that one can see what portion
 of budget is spent on which sub-utility).
 If all items indicate status - we should be able to tell by the total rank
 of every individual indicated by the function r (which depends on q and
 the of every category c of every quantity 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{i}$
\end_inset

 consumed as well as assets and income).
